7️⃣ Array Map Trick
console.log([1,2,3].map(parseInt));

Output

[1, NaN, NaN]
Why?

map() passes 3 arguments:

(value, index)

So it becomes:

parseInt(1,0) → 1
parseInt(2,1) → NaN
parseInt(3,2) → NaN